330
00:30:07,797 --> 00:30:10,380
He wants me to tell you that he
can't come over for lunch today.

331
00:30:10,464 --> 00:30:11,797
Oh.

332
00:30:11,880 --> 00:30:13,964
He said that your house
is too far away from his...

333
00:30:14,047 --> 00:30:16,005
and he's afraid of the blackouts.

334
00:30:25,297 --> 00:30:27,255
I have a message...

335
00:30:27,339 --> 00:30:29,672
for the mayor.

336
00:30:31,964 --> 00:30:33,880
"Your ship is in. "

337
00:30:49,630 --> 00:30:52,505
Good day, Messenger.

338
00:30:52,589 --> 00:30:55,589
What brings you to the Gathering Hall?

339
00:30:56,672 --> 00:30:58,797
I have a message for the mayor.

340
00:30:58,880 --> 00:31:00,505
Very good.

341
00:31:03,880 --> 00:31:06,547
Right this way, if you please.

342
00:31:10,880 --> 00:31:14,005
These pictures
are of all the mayors of Ember.

343
00:31:15,422 --> 00:31:17,339
I'm related to him.

344
00:31:17,422 --> 00:31:20,047
He was my great-great-

345
00:31:20,130 --> 00:31:23,505
I don't know how many "greats"-
