00:31:23,589 --> 00:31:27,422
"Podd Morethwart,
Seventh Mayor of Ember. "

347
00:31:28,505 --> 00:31:31,005
We still live in the same place he did.

348
00:31:32,089 --> 00:31:34,047
Mmm.

349
00:31:47,880 --> 00:31:49,797
<i>Come in.</i>

350
00:31:59,339 --> 00:32:01,839
I recognize you
from Assignment Day, don't I?

351
00:32:01,922 --> 00:32:05,630
She's a direct descendant
of our seventh mayor.

352
00:32:05,714 --> 00:32:08,880
Are you? How nice. Name?

353
00:32:08,964 --> 00:32:12,839
- Lina Mayfleet.
- "Mayfleet"?

354
00:32:12,922 --> 00:32:17,339
<i>That is a name for a Messenger.</i>

355
00:32:19,964 --> 00:32:22,922
May your feet be fleet.

356
00:32:29,255 --> 00:32:31,964
<i>Apparently,
you were born for the job.</i>

357
00:32:32,047 --> 00:32:34,047
What is your message for me,
Lina Mayfleet?

358
00:32:34,130 --> 00:32:36,505
It's from Looper, sir.

359
00:32:36,589 --> 00:32:39,089
Oh.

360
00:32:48,922 --> 00:32:51,130
"Your ship is in. "

361
00:32:53,755 --> 00:32:55,672
Excellent.

362
00:33:01,213 --> 00:33:04,172
What are those boxes
in the portraits, sir?

363
00:33:04,255 --> 00:33:07,130
<i>Is that part of the message?</i>

364
00:33:07,213 --> 00:33:09,797
No, I was just curious.

365
00:33:09,880 --> 00:33:12,422
Thank you.

366
00:33:16,838 --> 00:33:20,380
<i>Attention. Sewage spill
in Apartment Block 14.</i>

367
00:33:20,422 --> 00:33:22,755
<i>Plumbers and Bucketmen, be advised.</i>

368
00:33:22,838 --> 00:33:26,797
I'm just looking after myself. You've heard
the rumors. You know what they're saying.

369
00:33:26,880 --> 00:33:29,547
- It's going black for good.
- What's going black for good?

370
00:33:29,630 --> 00:33:31,838
Clean your ears, Little Miss Nosy.

371
00:33:31,922 --> 00:33:33,838
I said "back. "

372
00:33:33,922 --> 00:33:35,838
<i>Going back for good.</i>

