- Oh, shh.

495
00:46:07,504 --> 00:46:09,587
Please, honey.

496
00:46:09,671 --> 00:46:12,671
Don't do anything foolish.

497
00:46:12,754 --> 00:46:14,754
I couldn't bear to lose you too.

498
00:46:14,837 --> 00:46:16,962
How did he die, Clary?

499
00:46:17,046 --> 00:46:18,962
Oh.

500
00:46:20,046 --> 00:46:21,962
Did he really drown?

501
00:46:35,921 --> 00:46:39,504
Your father thought
it was doomsday too.

502
00:46:39,587 --> 00:46:42,546
<i>He believed there was a way
to get out of Ember.</i>

503
00:46:42,629 --> 00:46:45,421
<i>I couldn't dissuade him.</i>

504
00:46:45,504 --> 00:46:49,879
<i>I said it was our duty to stay here
and fix our problems...</i>

505
00:46:49,920 --> 00:46:52,545
that it's illegal to venture out
into the Unknown.

506
00:46:52,629 --> 00:46:54,337
Why is it illegal?

507
00:47:00,087 --> 00:47:04,295
Your father said,
"The river runs in one direction...

508
00:47:04,379 --> 00:47:09,462
<i>so it must come from someplace
and go to someplace. "</i>

509
00:47:09,545 --> 00:47:14,045
<i>But he must've hit it too early
or something. I- I don't know.</i>

510
00:47:14,129 --> 00:47:17,504
<i>The tunnel flooded, and-</i>

511
00:47:17,587 --> 00:47:21,254
<i>And my dad died.</i>

512
00:47:25,045 --> 00:47:27,629
He was by himself?

513
00:47:27,712 --> 00:47:31,337
Everyone else got out
before it collapsed.

514
00:47:37,295 --> 00:47:41,587
I was- I was considering
taking the box to the mayor.

515
00:47:41,670 --> 00:47:44,045
<i>Yes! Do that.</i>

516
00:47:44,129 --> 00:47:46,504
Do that instead, please.

517
00:47:46,587 --> 00:47:49,212
Let him handle the situation.

518
00:47:54,337 --> 00:47:56,629
<i>These are trying and troubled times.</i>

519
00:47:56,712 --> 00:48:00,462
Our problems are grave.

520
00:48:02,295 --> 00:48:04,295
We need answers.

521
00:48:04,379 --> 00:48:06,629
<i>But beyond answers-</i>

522
00:48:06,712 --> 00:48:10,587
more important than answers-

523
00:48:10,670 --> 00:48:13,045
we need solutions.

524
00:48:13,129 --> 00:48:15,045
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah.

525
00:48:15,129 --> 00:48:18,504
<i>And in order to find those solutions...</i>

526
00:48:20,420 --> 00:48:25,212
I propose we launch
a thorough investigation.

527
00:48:25,295 --> 00:48:27,379
Yes. Yes.

528
00:48:27,462 --> 00:48:31,295
I hereby declare
the creation of a task force...

529
00:48:31,379 --> 00:48:33,337
to investigate the blackouts.

530
00:48:38,337 --> 00:48:41,087
<i>Do I have volunteers?</i>

531
00:48:44,879 --> 00:48:49,837
Today we, the people...

532
00:48:49,920 --> 00:48:52,629
stand united against the darkness.

533
00:49:04,712 --> 00:49:06,504
My turn!

534
00:49:06,587 --> 00:49:09,045
Lizzie.

535
00:49:09,129 --> 00:49:10,879
Lizzie!

536
00:49:14,837 --> 00:49:17,837
<i>Hands off! Give me that!</i>

537
00:49:17,920 --> 00:49:20,087
- Peaches!
- All right! Go away!

538
00:49:20,170 --> 00:49:22,837
<i>Back off!</i>

539
00:49:22,920 --> 00:49:25,337
What's "applesauce"?

540
00:49:25,420 --> 00:49:27,462
<i>Hey, give me some!</i>

541
00:49:28,754 --> 00:49:30,594
Pineapple?

542
00:49:30,629 --> 00:49:32,504
- Give me that!
- Come on!

543
00:49:32,587 --> 00:49:36,420
No one's had pineapple since my grandmother
was a little girl. Where'd you get this?

544
00:49:36,504 --> 00:49:38,545
Give me that!

545
00:49:38,629 --> 00:49:41,087
Lizzie! Where'd you get that food?

546
00:49:43,295 --> 00:49:45,254
All right.

547
00:49:46,379 --> 00:49:49,170
I got it from my boyfriend.

548
00:49:49,254 --> 00:49:50,962
You don't have a boyfriend.

549
00:49:51,045 --> 00:49:54,212
It's not official, but there's this guy
who really likes me.

550
00:49:54,295 --> 00:49:58,045
He explores the storerooms,
especially the ones on the edges.

551
00:49:58,129 --> 00:50:00,962
They're marked empty in the ledger,
but they're not all empty.

552
00:50:01,045 --> 00:50:03,712
I'll give you a bite
if you promise not to tell.

553
00:50:06,587 --> 00:50:08,095
It's wrong, Lizzie.

554
00:50:08,096 --> 00:50:09,800
Well, he says it's all gonna
be gone soon anyway.

555
00:50:09,879 --> 00:50:12,212
Why not live as well
as we can right now?

556
00:50:12,295 --> 00:50:14,295
There he is.

557
00:50:25,837 --> 00:50:27,878
Doon!

558
00:50:27,962 --> 00:50:29,962
<i>Have you-</i>

559
00:50:33,128 --> 00:50:35,045
<i>Doon!</i>

560
00:50:40,045 --> 00:50:41,962
I need to tell you something.

561
00:50:42,045 --> 00:50:44,962
<i>It was Looper we saw
near that 351 door.</i>

562
00:50:45,045 --> 00:50:47,503
Before that, I took a message
to the mayor for him.

563
00:50:50,295 --> 00:50:53,295
<i>I'll bet there's something big
on the other side of that door.</i>

564
00:51:14,170 --> 00:51:16,170
<i>There's so much food.</i>

565
00:51:48,003 --> 00:51:49,920
Go.

566
00:51:59,920 --> 00:52:03,003
And I thought he was lying
when he talked about finding a solution.

567
00:52:03,087 --> 00:52:05,003
He wasn't lying.

568
00:52:05,087 --> 00:52:07,212
He's found his solution.

569
00:52:07,295 --> 00:52:09,628
Poppy. Lie down, okay?

570
00:52:09,712 --> 00:52:11,753
It's time to go to sleep.

571
00:52:11,837 --> 00:52:14,545
Could you just pump those pedals?

572
00:52:14,628 --> 00:52:16,837
What is this?

573
00:52:16,920 --> 00:52:20,503
It's the answering machine tape
from my parents' phone.

574
00:52:20,587 --> 00:52:22,628
When we still had one.

575
00:52:22,712 --> 00:52:26,045
Yoo-hoo. Yoo-hoo!

576
00:52:26,128 --> 00:52:28,045
Anybody home?

577
00:52:28,128 --> 00:52:31,628
<i>Don't hold dinner for me, darling.</i>

578
00:52:31,712 --> 00:52:33,712
<i>- That's my dad's voice.
- I'll be there before lights out.</i>

579
00:52:35,628 --> 00:52:39,878
Raine, it's me, Barrow.
I've been thinkin' about it.

580
00:52:39,962 --> 00:52:44,212
I watch my boy,
and... I've come around.

581
00:52:44,253 --> 00:52:47,837
I've changed my mind. I'm in.

582
00:52:48,962 --> 00:52:51,295
What's wrong?

583
00:52:55,128 --> 00:52:57,753
He lied to me.

584
00:52:57,837 --> 00:53:00,462
Where are you going?

585
00:53:00,545 --> 00:53:03,295
Well, meet me
at the Greenhouses, okay?

586
00:53:03,378 --> 00:53:05,795
<i>Good night, young man.</i>

587
00:53:05,878 --> 00:53:08,670
<i>How was your rehearsal?</i>

588
00:53:10,753 --> 00:53:13,212
For the Singing.

589
00:53:13,295 --> 00:53:16,753
Oh. I-It was fine.

590
00:53:16,837 --> 00:53:19,920
- It was really good.
- Good.

591
00:53:20,003 --> 00:53:23,003
<i>- Good night.
- Good night.</i>

592
00:53:25,712 --> 00:53:28,587
Dad. I heard you.

593
00:53:28,670 --> 00:53:30,753
<i>I heard you on the answering-</i>

594
00:53:30,837 --> 00:53:34,712
Lina Mayfleet has her parents'
old answering machine tape.

595
00:53:34,753 --> 00:53:37,587
I heard you.
You said her dad could count you in.

596
00:53:41,753 --> 00:53:44,462
You tried to leave the city, didn't you?

597
00:53:45,753 --> 00:53:48,253
W- Why would I do that?

598
00:53:48,336 --> 00:53:50,003
Because of me.

599
00:53:58,836 --> 00:54:00,711
Dad.

600
00:54:00,795 --> 00:54:02,711
<i>Please.</i>

601
00:54:05,336 --> 00:54:08,336
- We were wrong.
- No, you were right.

602
00:54:08,420 --> 00:54:10,336
There is an exit.

603
00:54:10,420 --> 00:54:13,628
Yeah. Raine thought so, too,
and it got him killed, Son.

604
00:54:13,711 --> 00:54:15,878
Dad, there's a way out
in the Pipeworks...

605
00:54:15,920 --> 00:54:18,003
but you have to tell me
everything that you know.

606
00:54:18,086 --> 00:54:21,420
- Tell me what you know.
- I don't know anything, and neither do you.

607
00:54:23,086 --> 00:54:25,045
<i>The Builders left Instructions.</i>

608
00:54:25,086 --> 00:54:27,128
The Builders abandoned us.

609
00:54:27,211 --> 00:54:29,961
No, they didn't.
They didn't, Dad. I have proof.

610
00:54:33,586 --> 00:54:35,461
Show me.

611
00:54:51,711 --> 00:54:54,336
Wait!

612
00:54:54,420 --> 00:54:57,336
Oh. Happy Great Day of Singing,
young lady.

613
00:54:57,420 --> 00:55:00,211
I need to speak to you in private.

614
00:55:00,295 --> 00:55:02,545
Very well then.

615
00:55:02,628 --> 00:55:06,045
What I need to tell you is secret
and really important.

616
00:55:06,128 --> 00:55:07,595
- What is it?
- The mayor-

617
00:55:07,596 --> 00:55:10,796
He's got a bunker in the Pipeworks.
It's filled with food.

618
00:55:13,211 --> 00:55:15,670
The shortages aren't as bad
as everyone thinks.

619
00:55:17,920 --> 00:55:21,003
You mean the mayor is stealing?

620
00:55:21,086 --> 00:55:24,378
Looper, who works in the storerooms,
is helping him.

621
00:55:26,878 --> 00:55:28,836
Well, this is shocking.

622
00:55:30,045 --> 00:55:33,503
Shocking. I'm shocked.

623
00:55:35,628 --> 00:55:38,961
Um, we have to report this.

624
00:55:39,045 --> 00:55:40,961
Come with me.

625
00:55:41,045 --> 00:55:43,051
Well done, Lina Mayfleet.

626
00:55:43,086 --> 00:55:45,170
Once you arrest him, Doon and I
can show you where the room is -

627
00:55:45,253 --> 00:55:47,711
<i>Wait. Where are we going?</i>

628
00:56:10,670 --> 00:56:12,545
I beg your pardon, Your Honor.

629
00:56:12,628 --> 00:56:16,170
<i>You remember Lina Mayfleet?</i>

630
00:56:16,253 --> 00:56:18,295
She wants to accuse you.

631
00:56:20,545 --> 00:56:22,461
Accuse me of what?

632
00:56:22,545 --> 00:56:24,711
Of stealing food
from the people of Ember.

633
00:56:26,878 --> 00:56:30,753
I love my city and everyone in it.

634
00:56:36,295 --> 00:56:38,295
And I would never think
to do such a thing.

635
00:56:38,378 --> 00:56:40,503
We saw your room!
We saw you in it!

636
00:56:41,670 --> 00:56:45,420
- "We"?
- She and her friend, Doon Harrow.

637
00:56:49,128 --> 00:56:52,045
What's that box?

638
00:56:52,128 --> 00:56:54,045
<i>Hmm.</i>

639
00:56:54,128 --> 00:56:56,045
It's mine.

640
00:56:57,503 --> 00:57:00,211
It's unusual looking.

641
00:57:00,295 --> 00:57:03,545
Where'd you get that?

642
00:57:07,586 --> 00:57:10,003
You're related to one of the mayors.

643
00:57:10,086 --> 00:57:12,545
Yes. Uh, he was the seventh mayor.

644
00:57:19,419 --> 00:57:22,628
A lot of things got lost
when the seventh mayor passed.

645
00:57:23,628 --> 00:57:25,628
May I look at that box, Lina?

646
00:57:25,711 --> 00:57:29,628
- Why?
- What's inside the box, Lina?

647
00:57:29,711 --> 00:57:33,836
I imagine it's official
mayor-related business.

648
00:57:35,128 --> 00:57:37,669
<i>Box. Give it to me.</i>

649
00:57:37,753 --> 00:57:40,253
- It's not yours.
- Give me the box!

650
00:57:40,336 --> 00:57:42,878
- No!
- Get it from her. Now.

651
00:57:43,919 --> 00:57:45,919
<i>Take it from her! Move!</i>

652
00:57:46,003 --> 00:57:48,294
<i>Grab her!</i>

653
00:57:48,378 --> 00:57:51,919
<i>Have you got her?</i>

654
00:58:11,169 --> 00:58:12,836
Get her.

655
00:58:25,919 --> 00:58:28,461
Stop! After her!

656
00:58:47,419 --> 00:58:50,336
Is this the home of Doon Harrow?

657
00:58:50,419 --> 00:58:52,544
Is he here?

658
00:58:52,628 --> 00:58:56,461
I- I-I can't hear. I have a weak ear.
Y- You have to talk louder.

659
00:58:56,544 --> 00:58:59,044
- Doon Harrow!
- Doon Harro- No, Loris.

660
00:58:59,128 --> 00:59:02,211
We're looking for Doon Harrow.
He's charged with treason against the city.

661
00:59:02,294 --> 00:59:05,919
That's terrible.
If it's true, he's no son of mine!

662
00:59:06,003 --> 00:59:08,461
<i>Treason is the worst offense
anyone could possibly commit.</i>

663
00:59:08,544 --> 00:59:12,669
Builders were wise when they said,
"If you have proof, you have to pursue it!

664
00:59:12,711 --> 00:59:16,544
<i>There's more to a bottle cap than
keeping liquid from leaking out of glass!"</i>

665
00:59:16,628 --> 00:59:18,461
- Get him!
- Uh, we'll go this way.

666
00:59:18,544 --> 00:59:22,211
Doon! The guards are here!
You traitor!

667
00:59:22,253 --> 00:59:24,586
- In here. Follow him.
- They're comin' to get you!

668
00:59:25,711 --> 00:59:27,919
The keypad is somewhere.

669
00:59:28,003 --> 00:59:30,211
What's he doin'?

670
00:59:30,253 --> 00:59:32,253
<i>- Just one second.
- He's crazy.</i>

671
00:59:32,336 --> 00:59:35,044
<i>- Is this the way to your apartment?
- Apparently not.</i>

672
00:59:47,794 --> 00:59:51,003
<i>Upstairs!</i>

673
01:00:00,253 --> 01:00:02,169
- They're after me!
- Who?

674
01:00:02,253 --> 01:00:04,169
- Guards!
- Why?

675
01:00:04,253 --> 01:00:06,294
<i>Doon and I, we- Quick.</i>

676
01:00:06,378 --> 01:00:09,419
<i>What is this all about?
We'll be late for the Great Day of Singing.</i>

677
01:00:09,503 --> 01:00:11,419
Well, excuse me, ma'am.

678
01:00:11,503 --> 01:00:13,628
I'm- I'm looking for Lina Mayfleet.

679
01:00:13,711 --> 01:00:15,961
Well, she's not here. She's probably
already in Harken Square.

680
01:00:16,044 --> 01:00:17,711
Okay, okay. Well, I guess
I'll just have a look for myself.

681
01:00:17,746 --> 01:00:19,419
Oh! Excuse me.

682
01:00:19,503 --> 01:00:22,211
Beg your pardon! So sorry.

683
01:00:25,294 --> 01:00:29,711
<i>You know, the mayor did
ask for her specifically.</i>

684
01:00:29,753 --> 01:00:32,961
The Greenhouse. Uh, she was meeting
a friend at the Greenhouse.

685
01:00:33,044 --> 01:00:34,961
<i>Does that help?</i>

686
01:01:04,336 --> 01:01:07,127
Careful!
That's food you're destroying!

687
01:01:07,211 --> 01:01:09,586
Our food!

688
01:01:13,461 --> 01:01:15,377
<i>Psst!</i>

689
01:01:38,211 --> 01:01:40,127
A warning:

690
01:01:40,211 --> 01:01:43,877
If I discover you were helping, harboring
or otherwise assisting those kids-

691
01:01:43,961 --> 01:01:45,961
Why would I do that?

692
01:01:49,586 --> 01:01:52,044
I have information
they were coming this way.

693
01:01:52,127 --> 01:01:54,127
Who provided you
with that information?

694
01:01:54,211 --> 01:01:56,627
That's confidential.

695
01:01:56,711 --> 01:02:01,169
All I need for you to understand is this:
If you're involved, you'll regret it.

696
01:02:02,877 --> 01:02:05,961
<i>Anything you hear, anything you see...</i>

697
01:02:06,044 --> 01:02:08,044
you tell me.

698
01:02:09,461 --> 01:02:11,419
Otherwise,
there will be consequences.

699
01:02:11,502 --> 01:02:16,211
Should anything happen in the future
that you hear of or see...

700
01:02:16,294 --> 01:02:18,211
<i>I'll expect to be informed.</i>

701
01:02:19,961 --> 01:02:21,961
I don't need to tell you
that I have the mayor's ear.

702
01:02:33,002 --> 01:02:35,002
<i>Hmm.</i>

703
01:03:01,669 --> 01:03:03,586
Okay.

704
01:03:03,669 --> 01:03:06,711
Leave two guards behind!

705
01:03:06,794 --> 01:03:09,336
We've gotta find a way out of here.

706
01:03:09,419 --> 01:03:11,294
Now.

707
01:03:18,711 --> 01:03:20,669
What is this?

708
01:03:29,836 --> 01:03:32,044
My dad made this.

709
01:03:35,002 --> 01:03:37,002
It doesn't look very safe.

710
01:03:37,086 --> 01:03:39,544
That's my dad.

711
01:03:43,586 --> 01:03:45,544
Everything he makes looks like this.

712
01:03:45,627 --> 01:03:47,961
What do you mean, your dad?

713
01:03:48,044 --> 01:03:51,627
Barrow. His voice is on
your answering machine.

714
01:03:51,711 --> 01:03:54,461
But your dad's name is Loris.

715
01:03:54,544 --> 01:03:57,961
Barrow Harrow. It's his nickname.

716
01:03:58,044 --> 01:04:00,877
- After some wheelbarrow he used to push around.
- You're the boy!

717
01:04:02,336 --> 01:04:05,002
That means our parents
were trying to escape together.

718
01:04:06,127 --> 01:04:08,627
They were trying.

719
01:04:08,711 --> 01:04:12,419
We're running out of time.
They'll come back for us.

720
01:04:29,335 --> 01:04:31,252
Pedal!

721
01:04:35,210 --> 01:04:38,294
Now, you stay here and be a good girl.

722
01:04:38,377 --> 01:04:40,585
Okay? And look for me up there.

723
01:04:40,669 --> 01:04:43,794
- Where's Lina?
- Oh, I'm- She's here somewhere.

724
01:04:48,544 --> 01:04:51,377
- Can you see anything?
- Barely.

725
01:05:03,877 --> 01:05:06,835
Here it is again-
the moment in the year...

726
01:05:06,877 --> 01:05:10,502
when we pause to celebrate
our fair city.

727
01:05:10,585 --> 01:05:12,919
This beacon of light...

728
01:05:13,002 --> 01:05:14,794
in a world of darkness.

729
01:05:16,210 --> 01:05:18,127
Hold on!

730
01:05:32,544 --> 01:05:34,460
Okay. That stuff- Cover it.

731
01:05:39,335 --> 01:05:41,585
This miracle of planning...

732
01:05:41,669 --> 01:05:44,710
<i>this magnificent achievement...</i>

733
01:05:44,794 --> 01:05:49,002
that is our city of Ember.

734
01:05:57,585 --> 01:06:00,169
* This is all we know *

735
01:06:00,252 --> 01:06:02,960
* Ember is forever *

736
01:06:03,044 --> 01:06:05,669
* When the light comes on *

737
01:06:05,710 --> 01:06:08,919
* I will be with you *

738
01:06:09,127 --> 01:06:11,794
* When the light comes on *

739
01:06:11,877 --> 01:06:14,835
* Hope is everlasting *

740
01:06:14,877 --> 01:06:16,585
They started singing.

741
01:06:16,669 --> 01:06:21,710
<i>* The morning light
Spend some time with you *</i>

742
01:06:24,710 --> 01:06:28,502
Oh, I've gotta show you.
The mayor had one too.

743
